Dialogue: 10,0:01:34.86,0:01:38.85,Top,,0,0,0,,The person I most respect—\Nthat is today’s theme.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.37,0:01:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Shakespeare, Churchill, Schweitzer—\Nhistory is full of such figures.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.40,0:01:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wish to speak of someone nearer, \Nsomeone far greater to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.68,0:01:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That person is my father.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.28,0:01:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is but a humble schoolmaster.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.08,0:02:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet he built a school for the blind.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.61,0:02:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In arts, mathematics, and even sports, \Nhe drew out the hidden gifts of his pupils,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.03,0:02:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and strove with all his strength to show them\Nthe joy of learning and the joy of living.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.53,0:02:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He has taught me how noble a calling\Nthe profession of teacher truly is.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.19,0:02:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, congratulations \Non winning the special prize! {????????? cant hear shit, juu***sho omedeto - could be something like "good presentation" but more likely sho = some award}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.08,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your speech outshone those of the fourth \Nand sixth forms many times over!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.59,0:02:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.69,0:02:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, you’ll help me \Nwith homework later, won’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.19,0:02:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Doris! That's sort of impudent, you know. {impudent; shameless; brazen; forward; audacious; cheeky}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.46,0:02:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all! Let’s work hard \Nin the prep room later.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.32,0:02:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurrah!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.38,0:02:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Top of the form in studies...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.40,0:02:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentle as the head girl of the class...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.50,0:02:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, Hilary is our greatest pride.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.63,0:03:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.60,0:03:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sleepy?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.68,0:03:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking of Dad.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.54,0:03:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,About your father?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.74,0:03:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When I leave St. Clare’s, \NI should like to be a teacher, like him.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.38,0:03:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Hilary—a teacher?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.55,0:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, your father will be overjoyed!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.38,0:03:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve not told him yet, not after what happened to my brother.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.76,0:03:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.69,0:03:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, he died in an accident.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.30,0:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeff was outstanding, \Nthe true pride of Father’s heart. {not in the book, so hoping it's just jeff and not some variation like geoff}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.44,0:03:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Father used to say every day:
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.07,0:04:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“My school, my dream that I spent \Nmy entire life creating, shall be Jeff’s to carry on.”
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.64,0:04:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, Dad doted on him.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.35,0:04:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I scarcely recall him ever playing with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.59,0:04:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Jeff died, it was as if Dad’s dream \Ncollapsed at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.06,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He was heartbroken.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:22.16,0:04:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I, I could do nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.99,0:04:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.34,0:04:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If there’s aught we can do, \Njay say the word.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.38,0:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, twins.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.25,0:04:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, are you awake?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.46,0:04:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.14,0:04:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then go straight to the Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.45,0:05:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, steel yourself and listen carefully.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.99,0:05:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.24,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A message came from your mother:
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.49,0:05:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,your father has collapsed.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.99,0:05:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.62,0:05:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.31,0:05:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.83,0:05:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How's dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.66,0:05:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Undergoing surgery. {/operation is in progress}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.54,0:05:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Il y a quatre saisons dans l'année: le printemps,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.56,0:05:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,l'été, l'automne et l'hiver. {There are four seasons in the year: spring, summer, autumn and winter.}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.85,0:05:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with you all?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.89,0:05:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive us, we're too worried \Nfor Hilary’s father.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.46,0:05:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As well you might.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:57.54,0:06:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how Hilary feels right about now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.33,0:06:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll pull through.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.84,0:06:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you agree, Mam'zelle?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.20,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s dismiss lessons for today.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.04,0:06:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are times when friendship and a human life\Nmatter more than any study.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.51,0:06:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us pray, with all our hearts.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.90,0:06:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls, I heard from Hilary just now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.32,0:06:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How is he?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:24.78,0:06:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The operation was a success.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.29,0:06:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Her father’s life is saved!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.27,0:06:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God! He was saved! \NI'm so happy for Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.69,0:06:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our prayers have been answered.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.72,0:06:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeff, where are you?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.94,0:06:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeff... Where is my Jeff?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.78,0:06:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Father...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.54,0:07:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor says he is making \Na miraculous recovery.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.64,0:07:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Thank Heaven!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.02,0:07:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.04,0:07:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, what is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.04,0:07:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the start of this year, you know \Nyour father’s school has been struggling.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.66,0:07:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes…
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.75,0:07:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One cannot charge the blind \Na great deal of money.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.18,0:07:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That was your father’s principle.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.86,0:07:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father has at last had \Nto give up the school.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.09,0:07:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.80,0:07:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.12,0:07:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We can no longer pay your tuition fees.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.27,0:07:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You will have to leave your school. {/quit}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.90,0:08:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:01.42,0:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is leaving St. Clare’s?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.40,0:08:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That can’t be true!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.62,0:08:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m afraid it’s confirmed.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.50,0:08:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh no...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.02,0:08:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, her mother called…
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.83,0:08:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.20,0:08:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.57,0:08:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Please,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.55,0:08:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,do something for Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.37,0:08:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve all leaned on Hilary in our hearts.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.22,0:08:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s not only a good learner;
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.35,0:08:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,she’s calm and kind...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.28,0:08:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and always thinking of helping her friends before herself!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.19,0:08:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If it’s money that’s needed, \Nplease grant Hilary a scholarship.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.09,0:08:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.86,0:08:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The rules say only the students who've reached at least the third form are eligible for a scholarship.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.10,0:08:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So Hilary cannot receive one?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.86,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Must she really go, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.72,0:09:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.44,0:09:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough, girls. \NLessons are about to begin.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.84,0:09:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to your classroom at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.02,0:09:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:13.45,0:09:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary said she wanted \Nto become a teacher herself,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:16.02,0:09:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so surely St. Clare's could lend her \Nan advance payment​? {?? my understanding is that they mean "hilary will work here after she graduates so you pay for her tuition from her future salary"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.91,0:09:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really both \Ncome up with the same idea? {?? unsure, maybe she means "thought the same thing as us"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.76,0:09:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, all things considered, it's a big stretch... {?? lit: no matter how much, such a thing...}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:24.92,0:09:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.43,0:09:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it, Headmistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:29.00,0:09:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, Patricia, financial matters \Nare not for you children to solve;
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.78,0:09:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,these are problems of the grown-up world.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.58,0:09:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, run along to your lessons.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.45,0:09:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How cold-hearted of Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.82,0:09:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought better of her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.09,0:09:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But perhaps, for once, it's truly beyond \Nwhat we children can do?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.44,0:09:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be! We've overcome so much \Nby friendship and teamwork before.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.70,0:10:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we shall now as well!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.72,0:10:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.72,0:10:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Pat, Isabel, you two \Nmight just be the ones who can help.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.22,0:10:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.83,0:10:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is a solicitor, isn't he? {/advocate/lawyer}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.72,0:10:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he can help Hilary’s father stay afloat? {?? not sure how}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.84,0:10:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly! Your father got to work at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.21,0:10:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, Mum?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.71,0:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary's father is a distinguished educator. {/teacher}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.06,0:10:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So he's going to explore whether some emergency funds could be raised by legal means.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.77,0:10:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know if it will succeed yet, \Nbut I’ll do whatever I can.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.51,0:10:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.64,0:10:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurrah!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.20,0:10:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For once, I feel obliged to join this plea. {lit: just this once, this request is from me as well}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.32,0:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A pupil brimming with appetite for learning \Nmust be protected come what may.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.52,0:10:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the duty of us who teach.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.98,0:11:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress, might there be some way?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.21,0:11:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... The twins' idea had some merit indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:06.43,0:11:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If only we could advance her salary \Nas a future teacher…
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.37,0:11:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I know not what can be done, \Nbut we will try every avenue.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.81,0:11:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, pure-hearted children
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.35,0:11:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,are powerless against \Nthe large machinery of society.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.85,0:11:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To shelter such children
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.87,0:11:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is our obligation as grown-ups.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.59,0:11:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallo, Hilary?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.24,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever comes, we are on your side.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.90,0:11:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:37.76,0:11:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And if ever you feel \Nyou cannot go on, think of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.84,0:11:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.27,0:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don’t feel ashamed \Nthat you can’t come to school any more. {sense of inferiority; one's weak point}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.54,0:11:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father has done \Nthe most wonderful work for the blind.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.01,0:11:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.73,0:11:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When we have a vacation, \Nwe’ll come to see him too.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.28,0:11:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Do come back to visit us at St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.18,0:11:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise us!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.03,0:12:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{>_>}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.06,0:12:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.46,0:12:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.41,0:12:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried only to hold fast to what I believed in.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.03,0:12:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet my dream is over now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.05,0:12:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Jeff... \NIf only he were still here…
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.54,0:12:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, dear. \NGet yourself together.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.78,0:12:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of the future rather than the past.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.30,0:12:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider how we can overcome this trouble.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.47,0:12:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.04,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. Forgive me.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:51.50,0:12:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We must keep our spirits up, \Nfor Hilary’s sake.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.47,0:12:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I have suffered enough; \Nyou all need not do so too. {lit: only me enduring painful thoughts is enough}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.35,0:13:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.27,0:13:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, should you be getting up yet? {meaning sitting up in bed}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:09.06,0:13:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am all right.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.72,0:13:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.32,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn’t fret about me.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:15.06,0:13:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a girl, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.58,0:13:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you shall be happy, that I vow. {only you will be happy im sure}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.54,0:13:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, did the doctor say how he is?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.98,0:13:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If he remains a fortnight in hospital, \Nhe should make a good recovery.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.11,0:13:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a comfort.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.35,0:13:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But losing the school \Nhas weighed upon him most of all.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.02,0:13:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Miss Roberts, do not tell my father \Nthat I must leave St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.13,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He blames himself for everything.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.56,0:13:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot bear to wound his pride further.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.67,0:13:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.84,0:14:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When they're on vacation, \NPat and the others will come here.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.54,0:14:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall let him know of that. {?? dunno why he needs to know that, maybe she means not to him}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.38,0:14:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're home!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.63,0:14:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.92,0:14:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.42,0:14:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.29,0:14:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We're grateful—to you and Dad,\Nfrom the bottom of our hearts!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.20,0:14:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it with you two?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.06,0:14:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of what happened to Hilary, \Nwe’ve realised how blessed we truly are.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.15,0:14:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to take going to school for granted.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.57,0:14:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We never considered that we owed being able to study at St. Clare’s to our parents.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.39,0:14:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.21,0:14:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we shall cherish every day at St. Clare’s!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.05,0:14:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's our last hope.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.95,0:14:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,If your Father can help Hilary, \Nwe shall learn the result today.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.66,0:14:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome home!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.09,0:14:55.20,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Welcome home!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.20,0:14:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m back.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.56,0:14:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.66,0:14:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.70,0:15:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I did everything in my power.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.19,0:15:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-Then, what of Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.98,0:15:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How... How can such a cruel thing happen?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:12.88,0:15:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Hilary should have \Nto leave school—how dreadful!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.70,0:15:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So cruel! \NGod is too cruel.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.72,0:15:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Pat, Isabel,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.76,0:15:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,many things befall folk in life.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.73,0:15:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One may strive hard, \Nbut trials and pain will come all the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.27,0:15:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet the word “hope” never dies \Nfrom the human heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.74,0:15:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hope?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.78,0:15:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You two, do endeavour \Nto kindle the flame of hope in Hilary’s heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:49.25,0:15:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.57,0:16:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.75,0:16:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! So you came?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.34,0:16:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you are absent from our classroom, \Nand in another city...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.31,0:16:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you shall always be \Nour head girl in our hearts.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.54,0:16:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.81,0:16:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.33,0:16:21.80,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.48,0:16:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We've missed you!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.30,0:16:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These are get well soon gifts! {lit: clare visit (to someone affected by illness or misfortune); call - here it's probs used in the sense "gifts for someone who is ill with wishes of quick recovery" - dunno how to fit this in}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.82,0:16:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And from me!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.55,0:16:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Cookies from me! {lit: I cookie - dunno, maybe she says "I want cookies"?}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:27.49,0:16:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Joan. {/as expected of}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.86,0:16:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.36,0:16:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.36,0:16:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If only a dunce like me \Ncould leave school in Hilary’s place...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.83,0:16:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why must Hilary be the one to leave St. Clare’s?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.90,0:16:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hush! You mustn’t say such things!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.32,0:16:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{Shh!}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.84,0:16:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary is leaving St. Clare’s?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.38,0:16:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.85,0:16:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.18,0:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.85,0:16:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.39,0:17:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear, what shall we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.56,0:17:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.88,0:17:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.56,0:17:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s dreadful! Hilary’s father...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.73,0:17:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.97,0:17:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mum! Where's Dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.67,0:17:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want it...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.94,0:17:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.53,0:17:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Father... Father, don’t be upset!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.35,0:17:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I leave St. Clare’s, \NI’ll still have Pat and Isabel and all the others.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.95,0:17:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll still be able to go on \Nstudying as hard as I can.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.12,0:17:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is my fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.62,0:17:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I poured my whole heart into my work, \Nwithout much care for anything else...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.06,0:17:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I have left my dearest daughter with nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.97,0:17:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.05,0:17:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I could do nothing for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.76,0:17:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No! That is not true.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.84,0:17:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}have{\i0} left me something—\Na wonderful way of living, in my heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.98,0:18:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let me say what I truly feel.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.39,0:18:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve kept it back all this time.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.82,0:18:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.04,0:18:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I was small, you only ever \Nspoke of your dreams to Jeff.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.58,0:18:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I was a girl, you told me nothing \Nof your work or your school.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.27,0:18:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so dreadfully lonely.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.77,0:18:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how hard I tried to talk, you always looked so busy and showed me only your back.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.18,0:18:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I loved your back, Father.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.42,0:18:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,For I saw how hard you worked, pouring the light \Nof hope upon the people who can't see on their own.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.26,0:18:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Your back was strong and broad, \Nand so I always thought—
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.54,0:18:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a teacher like you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.04,0:19:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, I want to carry on your dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.28,0:19:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll take up Jeff’s books in his place. {/do his share}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.78,0:19:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.50,0:19:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I always thought you were still a little girl...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.42,0:19:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was blind to everything—\Nboth how lonely you were,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.06,0:19:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how strong \Nand grown-up you had become.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.78,0:19:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary, you will one day be able \Nto rebuild your father’s school.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.79,0:19:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You shall be a fine teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.43,0:19:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, St. Clare’s will guide and nurture you.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.80,0:19:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.80,0:19:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.35,0:19:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.78,0:19:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I gained the approval \Nof the board of governors. {dunno if there can even be such a thing for school, but fuck if I know anything about private education; anyway this is literal}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.02,0:19:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,For any girl who wishes to be a teacher, \NSt. Clare’s will provide a special scholarship.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.00,0:20:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Such special scholarships only exist in a few selected schools, and in a very small number.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.84,0:20:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,At St. Clare’s, it was once proposed \Nin the former headmistress’s time,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.77,0:20:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but the board vetoed it \Nand it came to nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.24,0:20:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But today, our Headmistress overcame \Ntheir strong resistance with her splendid spirit!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.15,0:20:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Hilary Wentworth, what say you?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.36,0:20:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are firmly resolved to become a teacher, \Nand your parents give their consent,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.43,0:20:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,then you may go on \Nwith your studies at St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:35.65,0:20:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As for repayment, when you are a teacher, \Nyou may return the sum little by little each month.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.11,0:20:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.04,0:20:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall repay this kindness one day,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.55,0:20:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,by becoming a fine teacher \Nand rebuilding Father’s school,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.15,0:20:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,together with Father and Mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.95,0:20:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, we can achieve anything \Nif we put our strength together.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,For your dream is our dream too.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.16,0:21:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.57,0:21:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone! Thank you!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.56,0:21:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, Isabel, it is all thanks to you two.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.25,0:21:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.85,0:21:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Had you not come out \Nwith that outlandish idea,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.59,0:21:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I should never have thought \Nof that special scholarship.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.79,0:21:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Outlandish idea?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.49,0:21:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that Hilary might borrow \Nagainst her future teacher’s salary.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:37.23,0:21:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.00,0:21:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You two have lit a flame of hope \Nin Hilary’s family’s future.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.64,0:21:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid, both of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.44,0:21:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.31,0:21:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what’s the matter?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.71,0:21:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d usually be rushing about \Nlike a rocket telling everyone. {gotta be uchuusen = spaceship - no idea what she means, tho, very outlandish metaphor}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.91,0:21:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.82,0:21:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t our doing at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.63,0:21:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.15,0:22:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Hilary who was splendid.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.15,0:22:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And everyone else besides her.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.64,0:22:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oho, listen to that! {??? idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.56,0:22:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Putting on such airs!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.45,0:23:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.30,0:23:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To celebrate the opening of the new {swimming }pool, \Nthere’s to be a grand relay between the forms.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:40.89,0:23:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And our anchor in the first form \Nwill be Miss Roberts, our form mistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.39,0:23:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They say Miss Roberts is a splendid swimmer.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.40,0:23:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fifth form \Nhave some strong opponents.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.96,0:23:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Belinda, Pamela—and Miss Lewis too. \NA powerful line-up!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.82,0:23:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We shan’t lose! \NWe’ll fight for the championship!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.84,0:23:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.74,0:23:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.32,0:24:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“Bonjour in Bathing Suits.” {水着でボンジュール}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.32,0:24:03.79,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 20 \NBonjour in Bathing Suits {水着でボンジュール}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.64,0:24:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t miss it!
